# FutureState Agile Process

This project follows SAFe on the FLC FutureState program. **Always prefer local process docs over generic SAFe guidance.**

## Source of truth

1. `docs/futurestate-process.md` — consolidated summary (read first)
2. `reference/wiki/` — full wiki page exports (local; gitignored — run `scripts/sync_wiki.py`)
3. [Platform.wiki](https://dev.azure.com/FLC-NPD/FutureState/_wiki/wikis/Platform.wiki) — live wiki via Azure DevOps MCP

## Non-negotiables

- **Hierarchy:** Epic → Feature → User Story → Task
- **Timeboxes:** PI = 1 quarter (6 half-month iterations); Story/Task = 1 sprint; Feature = 1 PI
- **Story format:** As a [role], I want [goal] so that [benefit]
- **Platform governance:** User stories require Platform Decision and Rationale (*"It's Platform until it isn't"*)
- **States:** New → Active → Resolved → Closed; use Waiting for blockers (with comment)
- **Tags:** Apply governance tags (NeedsPO, NeedsAC, NeedsDoD, NeedsPI, NeedSAFe, NeedsScope)

## Tool routing

| Need | Tool |
|------|------|
| Backlog, iterations, capacity, PI planning boards | Azure DevOps MCP |
| Requirements, SRS/LiveDocs, reviews, traceability, test results | Polarion MCP |
| Process questions | `safe-process-navigator` skill |
| Refresh wiki exports | `wiki-sync` skill |

## Roles

- **Epic:** Business Owner, Architect, PM
- **Feature:** PM, PO
- **Story:** PO
- **Task:** Agile Team

Do not invent org-specific field names, iteration paths, or team names — query ADO or ask the user.
